WEBVTT

00:01.360 --> 00:03.102
[Sighs]

00:03.202 --> 00:09.949
♪♪

00:10.049 --> 00:16.795
♪♪

00:16.895 --> 00:23.602
♪♪

00:23.702 --> 00:25.564
Phil: Brannigan.

00:25.664 --> 00:27.606
Hey, Brannigan.
You still there?

00:27.706 --> 00:29.368
Brannigan: What do you
got for me, Big Phil?

00:29.468 --> 00:31.650
A dinner
with Franklin Roberts.

00:31.750 --> 00:33.652
What I'll do is, I can steer
the conversation

00:33.752 --> 00:35.534
towards the Logan case.

00:35.634 --> 00:36.976
Shouldn't be hard.

00:37.076 --> 00:39.078
Then I'll start digging.

01:40.419 --> 01:41.880
Be straight with me.

01:41.980 --> 01:43.802
When this ends, can you
go back to your family?

01:43.902 --> 01:45.804
Can I walk away?

01:45.904 --> 01:47.005
Of course.

01:47.105 --> 01:48.607
It's what we do.

01:48.707 --> 01:50.369
But, yeah,
I'll keep you posted.

01:50.469 --> 01:58.737
♪♪

01:58.837 --> 02:07.106
♪♪

02:07.206 --> 02:15.434
♪♪

02:15.534 --> 02:23.842
♪♪

02:23.942 --> 02:32.171
♪♪

02:32.271 --> 02:40.539
♪♪

02:40.639 --> 02:43.462
[Gun cocks]

02:43.562 --> 02:46.705
♪♪

02:46.805 --> 02:48.507
Yeah, yeah.

02:48.607 --> 02:56.435
♪♪

02:56.535 --> 02:57.836
No, no, no, no.

02:57.936 --> 02:59.558
No, you -- you shoot me --
Shut up, man!

02:59.658 --> 03:00.919
Don't even.

03:01.019 --> 03:05.504
You shoot him, you'll --
you'll never know.

03:08.787 --> 03:11.410
You'll never know.

03:11.510 --> 03:14.893
Know what?

03:14.993 --> 03:16.495
Know what?!

03:16.595 --> 03:19.578
♪♪

03:19.678 --> 03:21.940
♪ Chicago ♪

03:22.040 --> 03:24.583
♪ Where the dollar and
blue collar go hand in hand ♪

03:24.683 --> 03:27.025
♪ City of Dreams so big ♪

03:27.125 --> 03:29.828
♪ Nightmares don't stand
a chance ♪

03:29.928 --> 03:32.871
♪ A concrete paradise
where roses grow ♪

03:32.971 --> 03:34.353
♪ See the smile from a child ♪

03:34.453 --> 03:35.914
♪ Light up
the Magnificent Mile ♪

03:36.014 --> 03:37.756
♪ And melt the coldest snow ♪

03:37.856 --> 03:39.478
♪ This is home ♪

03:39.578 --> 03:42.241
♪ Find the brightest minds
on these dark streets ♪

03:42.341 --> 03:45.123
♪ See the heart and soul
on these old blocks ♪

03:45.223 --> 03:47.246
♪ Where we grow,
we call it the Go ♪

03:47.346 --> 03:49.908
♪ 'Cause we don't stop ♪

03:56.755 --> 03:58.737
[Beep]

03:58.837 --> 04:00.579
Brannigan:
The Nation's take is down,

04:00.679 --> 04:04.383
which means our cut is down,
all because big man Dante

04:04.483 --> 04:07.946
has his eye
on legitimate business shit.

04:08.046 --> 04:11.950
I'm thinking maybe we go
back to the Faction.

04:12.050 --> 04:14.032
I'm thinking

04:14.132 --> 04:17.956
that's at the heart
of who you are, isn't it?

04:18.056 --> 04:20.639
Loyalty.
Am I right?

04:20.739 --> 04:23.842
Do you think
Lieutenant Brannigan

04:23.942 --> 04:25.884
is a loyal kind of guy?
Shut up!

04:25.984 --> 04:29.848
T-T-That's not even
the biggest question.

04:29.948 --> 04:32.931
Don't think about
saving Brannigan.

04:33.031 --> 04:35.013
There's a bigger
picture here.

04:35.113 --> 04:37.576
Before you decide
what to do,

04:37.676 --> 04:40.459
let me ask you something,
real bottom line.

04:40.559 --> 04:42.861
Which are you first?

04:42.961 --> 04:46.705
Are you Nation
or are you a Black man?

04:46.805 --> 04:49.468
Loyalty to who?

04:49.568 --> 04:53.312
To all brothers and sisters
across America

04:53.412 --> 04:57.276
or to a select few

04:57.376 --> 05:01.159
selling junk
on Cottage Grove?

05:01.259 --> 05:07.966
♪♪

05:08.066 --> 05:14.733
♪♪

05:14.833 --> 05:21.600
♪♪

05:25.364 --> 05:27.806
[Horns honking, traffic noise]

05:34.973 --> 05:42.681
♪♪

05:42.781 --> 05:51.290
♪♪

05:51.390 --> 05:52.811
♪♪

05:52.911 --> 05:55.694
[Cellphone rings]

05:55.794 --> 05:56.735
Phil: Hey.

05:56.835 --> 05:59.177
Hey.
Where are you?

05:59.277 --> 06:00.979
Over at Englewood
High School.

06:01.079 --> 06:03.862
Yeah, they got a blockage
in the staff restroom, and --

06:03.962 --> 06:06.024
You okay?
Yeah.

06:06.124 --> 06:07.666
Joshua w--

06:07.766 --> 06:09.308
No, he's good.
Trust me, he's good.

06:09.408 --> 06:10.869
But, uh, he can't talk
right now,

06:10.969 --> 06:12.351
'cause, uh, well,

06:12.451 --> 06:15.474
the boy's installing
an anti-siphon valve.

06:15.574 --> 06:17.115
You know, how about that?

06:17.215 --> 06:19.398
I mean, I'm starting
to think of, uh --

06:19.498 --> 06:21.780
I think he actually likes
this line of work.

06:24.663 --> 06:25.924
You think so?

06:26.024 --> 06:30.849
♪♪

06:30.949 --> 06:35.694
♪♪

06:35.794 --> 06:37.796
[Door unlocks]

06:39.397 --> 06:41.399
[Door opens]

06:44.082 --> 06:45.143
Hey, Ma.

06:45.243 --> 06:47.185
Hey.

06:47.285 --> 06:49.027
Phil not with you?

06:49.127 --> 06:50.749
Uh, no. He went to his place
to get changed.

06:50.849 --> 06:51.830
Oh, yeah?

06:51.930 --> 06:54.232
Yep.

06:54.332 --> 06:55.954
Where were you today?

06:56.054 --> 06:57.516
Uh, Englewood High.

06:57.616 --> 06:59.237
All day?
Yep.

06:59.337 --> 07:01.500
I was learning how to put on
an anti-siphon valve.

07:03.742 --> 07:06.445
And then Phil
dropped you home?

07:06.545 --> 07:07.726
Yep.

07:07.826 --> 07:10.769
What'd you have
for lunch?

07:10.869 --> 07:14.092
I don't remember.

07:14.192 --> 07:16.194
Maybe it was Lucky's
on Cottage Grove.

07:18.396 --> 07:20.379
What is this?

07:20.479 --> 07:22.901
You tell me what this is,
Joshua.

07:23.001 --> 07:25.484
Why don't you tell me
what this is?

07:27.646 --> 07:30.188
What? Dante Blake had
a blocked drain

07:30.288 --> 07:32.391
he needed you to fix?

07:32.491 --> 07:34.393
So you're lying
to your mama now.

07:34.493 --> 07:36.995
Huh? We don't do that
in this house.

07:37.095 --> 07:38.236
I'm the liar?

07:38.336 --> 07:39.357
Joshua, listen --
It's your boyfriend.

07:39.457 --> 07:41.039
No, I get it.
I know.

07:41.139 --> 07:42.501
He's covering for you,
and he's colluding
with you in this,

07:42.581 --> 07:43.722
and I don't like it either.
But he's not here.

07:43.822 --> 07:45.203
We're talking about you
right now.

07:45.303 --> 07:46.645
Ma --
So don't go dodging
your problem,

07:46.745 --> 07:48.126
trying to shift it
onto other people's plates.

07:48.226 --> 07:50.048
Ma!
What have I
always told you?

07:50.148 --> 07:51.970
Take responsibility,
own your shit!

07:52.070 --> 07:54.573
Okay! Okay!
So go ahead, let me hear it!

07:54.673 --> 07:55.654
Let me hear it!

07:55.754 --> 07:59.057
He's a cop.

07:59.157 --> 08:01.099
[Scoffs]

08:01.199 --> 08:02.541
What are you
talking about?

08:02.641 --> 08:04.182
Who?

08:04.282 --> 08:09.668
♪♪

08:09.768 --> 08:11.710
Who's a cop, Joshua?

08:11.810 --> 08:16.034
♪♪

08:16.134 --> 08:17.115
Phil.

08:17.215 --> 08:21.840
♪♪

08:21.940 --> 08:23.642
Okay?

08:23.742 --> 08:25.524
He a cop.

08:25.624 --> 08:29.568
♪♪

08:29.668 --> 08:31.209
Good.

08:31.309 --> 08:39.017
♪♪

08:39.117 --> 08:41.179
You --

08:41.279 --> 08:42.861
Norma: So you both knew
and you didn't tell me.

08:42.961 --> 08:44.302
Franklin:
I need you to just --
I'm pregnant!

08:44.402 --> 08:45.864
I'm having
this man's baby!

08:45.964 --> 08:48.186
You -- you knew this
and you still didn't tell me?!

08:48.286 --> 08:49.868
Our whole strategy
was around --

08:49.968 --> 08:53.391
Strategy?!
Strategy?!

08:53.491 --> 08:55.193
Are you fucking kidding me,
Franklin?

08:55.293 --> 08:57.395
No, no, no.
What is wrong with you,
Franklin?!

08:57.495 --> 08:59.718
Why would you even use
a word like that?!

08:59.818 --> 09:01.239
Everything turns on this,
everything.

09:01.339 --> 09:02.561
It's what they do.
It's -- it's who they are.

09:02.661 --> 09:04.362
It's what we're trying
to change, Norma.

09:04.462 --> 09:06.164
This is me, Franklin.

09:06.264 --> 09:07.726
This is me!

09:07.826 --> 09:13.411
♪♪

09:13.511 --> 09:16.875
I need --
I need three days.

09:19.077 --> 09:20.098
I know. I know.

09:20.198 --> 09:23.141
How dare you?

09:23.241 --> 09:25.383
How dare you make me
a part of your strategy

09:25.483 --> 09:27.485
and not tell me?

09:29.327 --> 09:30.749
Do you know
what that feels like?

09:30.849 --> 09:32.150
I'm sorry.

09:32.250 --> 09:33.552
The way he --
he violated me,

09:33.652 --> 09:35.073
and you allowed him
to do that.

09:35.173 --> 09:36.755
I know.
Jesus Christ.

09:36.855 --> 09:38.316
Mom --
What?!

09:38.416 --> 09:39.918
No, no. Norma, Norma.
What?!

09:40.018 --> 09:41.119
Three days.
I need three days.

09:41.219 --> 09:43.241
Please.
I got it right with Moses

09:43.341 --> 09:44.603
when everybody thought
I was wrong.

09:44.703 --> 09:46.164
I got it right.
You were the strength.

09:46.264 --> 09:48.286
We saved him together.
Norma, I'm begging you.

09:48.386 --> 09:50.248
[Cellphone ringing]
I'm begging you.

09:50.348 --> 09:51.890
I'm begging you, Norma.
Please.

09:51.990 --> 09:54.653
Please, Norma.

09:54.753 --> 09:57.656
I'm begging you.

09:57.756 --> 10:00.458
Phil: Norma?

10:00.558 --> 10:01.740
Norma?

10:01.840 --> 10:03.782
Yeah, I'm here.

10:03.882 --> 10:05.584
Well, you alright?
Something wrong?

10:05.684 --> 10:08.547
♪♪

10:08.647 --> 10:10.508
[Whispers] Norma.

10:10.608 --> 10:12.711
Norma.

10:12.811 --> 10:14.392
Just a little nauseous.

10:14.492 --> 10:17.235
[Chuckling]

10:17.335 --> 10:19.638
Well, you know
that's normal, right?

10:19.738 --> 10:21.039
Sure.

10:21.139 --> 10:25.123
♪♪

10:25.223 --> 10:26.444
[Sniffles softly]

10:26.544 --> 10:28.126
Yeah, I can't make it
over tonight.

10:28.226 --> 10:31.890
♪♪

10:31.990 --> 10:33.451
Yeah?
Yeah, yeah.

10:33.551 --> 10:36.935
I mean, I'm sorry.
Uh, just something that came up.

10:37.035 --> 10:39.858
So --
What's that?

10:39.958 --> 10:41.700
Yeah, uh [clears throat]
it's a job

10:41.800 --> 10:43.061
I got for a friend, and I --

10:43.161 --> 10:45.143
Well, I should have
done it weeks ago.

10:45.243 --> 10:47.145
But I -- But I'll still pick up
Josh in the morning.

10:47.245 --> 10:48.546
Then I'll -- I guess

10:48.646 --> 10:50.648
I'll see you for dinner
with Franklin.

10:53.371 --> 10:54.993
Norma?

10:55.093 --> 10:58.917
Sure.

10:59.017 --> 11:01.019
Love you.
See you soon.

11:03.461 --> 11:05.604
[Call ends]

11:05.704 --> 11:07.706
[Cellphone drops]

11:18.036 --> 11:19.978
Joshua: Ma.

11:20.078 --> 11:22.961
Look, Ma,
I'm -- I'm sorry.

11:24.803 --> 11:26.805
Okay?

11:29.968 --> 11:32.130
I thought what I had
with Phil was real.

11:36.134 --> 11:38.136
How could I be so wrong?

11:41.179 --> 11:42.681
I don't know.

11:42.781 --> 11:48.486
♪♪

11:48.586 --> 11:50.588
Where do we go
from here, Jojo?

11:54.032 --> 11:55.613
How do we trust
each other now?

11:55.713 --> 12:00.979
♪♪

12:01.079 --> 12:06.344
♪♪

12:06.444 --> 12:09.467
Ma.

12:09.567 --> 12:11.029
Ma.

12:11.129 --> 12:18.196
♪♪

12:18.296 --> 12:24.642
♪♪

12:24.742 --> 12:31.229
♪♪

12:34.793 --> 12:38.997
Franklin: No, no. No, no, no.
Nicole: Yes, yes.

12:41.800 --> 12:43.882
Nicole.
Nicole.

12:46.805 --> 12:48.807
Shoeshine?

12:50.568 --> 12:51.790
I like your boots.

12:51.890 --> 12:53.551
Never take them off.

12:53.651 --> 12:56.194
That's how I feel
about my Doc Martens.

12:56.294 --> 12:58.596
Only thing the Brits
ever got right.

12:58.696 --> 13:01.359
Got them on a trip to London
15 years ago.

13:01.459 --> 13:03.441
Great little store
in Camden Town.

13:03.541 --> 13:04.923
Good
working-man's shoes.

13:05.023 --> 13:06.925
Shakespeare.

13:07.025 --> 13:08.246
Excuse me?

13:08.346 --> 13:09.287
The Beatles.

13:09.387 --> 13:11.129
Liverpool Football Club.

13:11.229 --> 13:12.290
Canterbury Cathedral.

13:12.390 --> 13:13.491
National Health Service.

13:13.591 --> 13:15.693
The miniskirt.
My grandparents.

13:15.793 --> 13:18.496
One or two other things
the Brits got right.

13:18.596 --> 13:22.260
♪♪

13:22.360 --> 13:24.262
Good morning, Lieutenant.

13:24.362 --> 13:25.824
Counselor.

13:25.924 --> 13:31.069
♪♪

13:31.169 --> 13:36.314
♪♪

13:36.414 --> 13:38.416
I have a confession.

13:40.738 --> 13:43.561
This is personal.

13:43.661 --> 13:47.445
I'm not your usual
zealot prosecutor.

13:47.545 --> 13:49.607
I don't want to put people
in cages forever

13:49.707 --> 13:52.370
just because I can.

13:52.470 --> 13:56.174
But -- and it's a really big
"but"

13:56.274 --> 13:59.417
and it's why
I'm standing here today --

13:59.517 --> 14:02.941
when I see somebody who's been
given civic responsibility

14:03.041 --> 14:04.823
and a sacred duty of care

14:04.923 --> 14:08.366
to look after people
do a thing like this...

14:13.451 --> 14:16.554
...you better know
I'm coming for you.

14:16.654 --> 14:19.137
And here's the really big news.

14:20.778 --> 14:23.501
So's the organisation
you work for.

14:27.145 --> 14:29.848
The CPD has changed.

14:29.948 --> 14:33.211
This is an institution that
has learned from its mistakes

14:33.311 --> 14:35.733
and is prepared to say, "No.

14:35.833 --> 14:37.255
Enough is enough.

14:37.355 --> 14:38.776
We won't have it anymore

14:38.876 --> 14:42.620
when a colleague behaves
in this appalling way."

14:42.720 --> 14:47.425
George Floyd has made
a difference.

14:47.525 --> 14:51.389
The fact that this prosecution
stands on the testimony

14:51.489 --> 14:54.272
of the accused's
brother officers

14:54.372 --> 14:58.076
tells you so much about
the new world we're moving into

14:58.176 --> 15:01.419
after what happened
in Minneapolis two summers ago.

15:03.461 --> 15:07.505
Officer Logan is a bad apple
in the barrel.

15:08.746 --> 15:13.211
It's my job and it's your job

15:13.311 --> 15:16.534
and it's the job of everyone
who worked with him

15:16.634 --> 15:18.456
to remove that bad apple.

15:18.556 --> 15:25.343
♪♪

15:25.443 --> 15:27.145
[Indistinct conversations]

15:27.245 --> 15:30.588
Pretty, uh,
rarefied up there.

15:30.688 --> 15:31.789
What's that?

15:31.889 --> 15:33.631
The moral high ground.

15:33.731 --> 15:36.915
Not much oxygen for you folks
who just discovered racism.

15:37.015 --> 15:39.637
Don't tell me who I am
and who I'm not.

15:39.737 --> 15:42.080
I'm comfortable with
the moral map I live by.

15:42.180 --> 15:44.042
You said this was personal.
You meant that?

15:44.142 --> 15:45.603
Tell you what.

15:45.703 --> 15:48.967
Gloves off in there,
and then why don't we be

15:49.067 --> 15:51.729
civil to each other
outside of court?

15:51.829 --> 15:54.973
What do you say,
Franklin?

15:55.073 --> 15:56.975
I say no.

15:57.075 --> 15:58.616
I can't compartmentalise
like that.

15:58.716 --> 16:01.179
That's not who I am.

16:01.279 --> 16:02.740
You know,
a couple of years ago,

16:02.840 --> 16:05.503
I heard a spokesman from the
Labor Party in Britain say,

16:05.603 --> 16:07.465
"We've always been
anti-racist

16:07.565 --> 16:11.469
and we've always been
anti-Semitic."

16:11.569 --> 16:14.592
I don't know, of course,
but I think he got it all wrong

16:14.692 --> 16:16.955
because the words
were new to him

16:17.055 --> 16:20.638
and they didn't quite fit
in his mouth yet.

16:20.738 --> 16:22.740
Are you comparing me
to him?

16:25.903 --> 16:30.528
That level of arrogance,
bigotry

16:30.628 --> 16:32.570
reminds me of something.

16:32.670 --> 16:38.856
♪♪

16:38.956 --> 16:42.440
My opponent gave me
a list of witnesses.

16:44.402 --> 16:48.306
It's a long list of mostly
police officers,

16:48.406 --> 16:52.670
who she's suggesting are here
to clean up their institution

16:52.770 --> 16:54.912
and cleanse their souls

16:55.012 --> 16:59.597
by condemning Officer Logan
for what he did.

16:59.697 --> 17:02.520
But there's one name
not on the list,

17:02.620 --> 17:05.283
the one person closest
to the experience

17:05.383 --> 17:07.005
of this racist murder,

17:07.105 --> 17:11.849
and they -- she has decided
you don't need to hear from her.

17:11.949 --> 17:14.452
The witness is in court.

17:14.552 --> 17:16.254
She's sitting right there.

17:16.354 --> 17:18.696
Her name is Naimah Watts.

17:18.796 --> 17:21.859
Her husband was Jalil Watts.

17:21.959 --> 17:25.063
She's in court,
but she won't be on the stand.

17:25.163 --> 17:28.546
Now, why do you think that is?

17:28.646 --> 17:31.189
If you're State's Attorney
Pearson prosecuting a murder

17:31.289 --> 17:35.033
with all that righteousness
on your side,

17:35.133 --> 17:38.556
isn't it a good idea for the
grief-stricken family member

17:38.656 --> 17:42.400
to tell you,
the jury, about her pain?

17:42.500 --> 17:44.482
But, somehow,
Ms. Pearson has decided

17:44.582 --> 17:49.607
that Naimah's loss
is not a part of this story.

17:49.707 --> 17:51.089
Why not?

17:51.189 --> 17:53.531
Why no Naimah?

17:53.631 --> 17:55.613
Because the same police
department

17:55.713 --> 17:59.737
my opponent asks you to believe
is reforming itself

17:59.837 --> 18:03.061
as we speak was not
even remotely interested

18:03.161 --> 18:06.504
in investigating the brutal
beating of her husband

18:06.604 --> 18:12.230
outside a bar habituated
solely by police officers.

18:12.330 --> 18:15.793
Why is she not calling Naimah?

18:15.893 --> 18:18.076
How dare she put up a photograph
of a smashed-up face,

18:18.176 --> 18:20.958
with a bashed-in head
and claim she's on his side.

18:21.058 --> 18:23.401
And everyone who made it
possible for this

18:23.501 --> 18:25.283
to happen to another innocent
Black man

18:25.383 --> 18:27.765
is now on the right side
of the argument?

18:27.865 --> 18:29.047
No, no, no, no.

18:29.147 --> 18:30.808
No, we've had enough
of being told

18:30.908 --> 18:32.770
how the world
looks by White people,

18:32.870 --> 18:35.093
and we won't take
the same people telling us

18:35.193 --> 18:37.655
that 22 years for the man
who murdered a brother

18:37.755 --> 18:39.977
in broad daylight
in downtown Minneapolis

18:40.077 --> 18:42.460
and then told the world
he did nothing wrong

18:42.560 --> 18:45.423
somehow corrects 400 years

18:45.523 --> 18:48.506
of the systematic dehumanising
of our people.

18:48.606 --> 18:51.429
How dare she stand there
and claim

18:51.529 --> 18:56.974
she's on the side of angels
coming down for the bad apple?

19:00.418 --> 19:04.001
But I know why she's doing it.

19:04.101 --> 19:07.325
I see her.

19:07.425 --> 19:09.127
She doesn't want to feel guilty.

19:09.227 --> 19:12.210
She doesn't want you
to feel guilty.

19:12.310 --> 19:13.531
She wants to be able to say,

19:13.631 --> 19:14.972
"There's nothing wrong
with the world

19:15.072 --> 19:17.795
as long as we cut down
some rotten fruit."

19:20.598 --> 19:24.342
She wants this to be personal.

19:24.442 --> 19:26.063
Okay.

19:26.163 --> 19:28.946
Let's be personal.

19:29.046 --> 19:35.233
If she thinks this trial is
about one individual, one cop,

19:35.333 --> 19:37.335
then she's a part
of the problem.

19:39.777 --> 19:41.779
No, it's bigger than that.

19:43.741 --> 19:48.746
If she thinks this trial is
about one individual, one cop...

19:51.349 --> 19:56.093
...then she is the problem.

19:56.193 --> 20:00.878
♪♪

20:04.562 --> 20:07.505
♪ Every Sunday morning ♪

20:07.605 --> 20:11.369
♪ Mama made us go to church ♪

20:12.610 --> 20:14.392
Yo, I'll pick you up
at 5:00 right here.

20:14.492 --> 20:16.194
♪ It got down inside of us ♪

20:16.294 --> 20:19.076
♪ And now it's time to work ♪

20:19.176 --> 20:21.879
♪ This is the time ♪

20:21.979 --> 20:28.045
♪ To tell somebody
about the good news ♪

20:28.145 --> 20:30.047
♪ Wake up and ♪

20:30.147 --> 20:38.176
♪♪

20:38.276 --> 20:46.344
♪♪

20:46.444 --> 20:54.472
♪♪

20:54.572 --> 21:02.600
♪♪

21:02.700 --> 21:10.768
♪♪

21:10.868 --> 21:18.936
♪♪

21:19.036 --> 21:27.024
♪♪

21:27.124 --> 21:29.307
[Vehicle door closes,
engine starts]

21:29.407 --> 21:35.112
♪♪

21:35.212 --> 21:40.918
♪♪

21:41.018 --> 21:46.724
♪♪

21:46.824 --> 21:52.490
♪♪

21:52.590 --> 21:58.296
♪♪

21:58.396 --> 22:02.300
[Children playing]

22:02.400 --> 22:07.265
♪♪

22:07.365 --> 22:12.189
♪♪

22:12.289 --> 22:17.154
♪♪

22:17.254 --> 22:18.916
[Gasping]

22:19.016 --> 22:24.041
♪♪

22:24.141 --> 22:26.764
Did you know
who he was?

22:26.864 --> 22:29.327
Other than
he was a cop, no.

22:29.427 --> 22:33.170
Well, how did you know
he was a cop?

22:33.270 --> 22:35.533
How they walk,
the way they move.

22:35.633 --> 22:37.695
They have
that cop atmosphere.

22:37.795 --> 22:39.457
Was he alone?

22:39.557 --> 22:41.619
Yes.

22:41.719 --> 22:45.062
Did he do any police work
while he was at the hospital?

22:45.162 --> 22:46.384
No.

22:46.484 --> 22:48.866
Did he talk
to Jalil's family?

22:48.966 --> 22:49.987
No.

22:50.087 --> 22:51.188
Did he ask to?

22:51.288 --> 22:53.070
I mentioned his wife
was coming back.

22:53.170 --> 22:56.233
That's when he left.

22:56.333 --> 22:59.517
How was he behaving
when you first saw him,

22:59.617 --> 23:00.758
before he saw you?

23:00.858 --> 23:05.443
Shifty, furtive,
a little crazy,

23:05.543 --> 23:08.926
like he hadn't slept
in a long time.

23:09.026 --> 23:10.528
Main thing --

23:10.628 --> 23:14.031
he clearly didn't want anyone
to clock him being there.

23:15.953 --> 23:20.317
Let me ask you
about the injuries to Jalil.

23:23.641 --> 23:27.064
I've seen a lot
during my time on this job.

23:27.164 --> 23:28.225
Mm-hmm.

23:28.325 --> 23:30.147
County can be
like a war zone.

23:30.247 --> 23:34.512
The violence people do
to other people.

23:34.612 --> 23:39.757
This may be the most
brutal assault I've seen.

23:39.857 --> 23:43.080
And how did that
make you feel?

23:43.180 --> 23:45.603
I used to feel angry.

23:45.703 --> 23:48.125
And now?

23:48.225 --> 23:50.207
Tired.

23:50.307 --> 23:53.931
Very, very tired.

23:54.031 --> 23:55.973
Do you want
to feel that way?

23:56.073 --> 23:57.935
No, I don't.

23:58.035 --> 23:59.817
Hmm.

23:59.917 --> 24:03.260
Can I ask you
a question?

24:03.360 --> 24:05.963
Please.
Go ahead.

24:08.285 --> 24:11.348
Representing
a monster like him...

24:11.448 --> 24:15.112
♪♪

24:15.212 --> 24:18.436
...how do you look at yourself
in the mirror?

24:18.536 --> 24:23.961
♪♪

24:24.061 --> 24:26.524
By asking everyone else

24:26.624 --> 24:28.966
to look
in the mirror with me.

24:29.066 --> 24:36.013
♪♪

24:36.113 --> 24:44.902
♪♪

24:45.002 --> 24:52.550
♪♪

24:52.650 --> 25:00.838
♪♪

25:00.938 --> 25:05.803
♪♪

25:05.903 --> 25:08.045
[Sobbing]

25:08.145 --> 25:13.290
♪♪

25:13.390 --> 25:18.496
♪♪

25:18.596 --> 25:21.218
Can you tell us how
discovering Jalil Watts

25:21.318 --> 25:23.340
lying wounded on the street
that night

25:23.440 --> 25:25.943
has affected you?

25:26.043 --> 25:28.225
I'm woken in the night,
every night,

25:28.325 --> 25:32.950
by the nightmare
I always have.

25:33.050 --> 25:34.271
And I wake up
in the morning

25:34.371 --> 25:36.934
to a day of thinking
about nothing else.

25:38.656 --> 25:41.238
It's what I see
all the time.

25:41.338 --> 25:44.121
What do you see?

25:44.221 --> 25:49.727
His head
all ballooned up...

25:49.827 --> 25:51.649
and the blood.

25:51.749 --> 25:54.371
[Sniffles]

25:54.471 --> 25:57.254
I'm sorry.
Why is this even a trial, huh?

25:57.354 --> 25:58.976
He's not saying
it wasn't him.

25:59.076 --> 26:01.058
Not even saying he was
attacked or anything.

26:01.158 --> 26:02.860
So, frankly,
what the fuck?!

26:02.960 --> 26:05.663
[Spectators murmuring]

26:05.763 --> 26:07.865
Can I say that?

26:07.965 --> 26:09.967
I think you just did.

26:12.049 --> 26:14.992
That's how I feel.

26:15.092 --> 26:18.035
Franklin: Why did you
leave the scene?

26:18.135 --> 26:20.758
You could see
he wasn't dead.

26:20.858 --> 26:23.881
I didn't want
to get involved.

26:23.981 --> 26:24.922
Why not?

26:25.022 --> 26:27.525
I was scared.

26:27.625 --> 26:30.728
Of what?

26:30.828 --> 26:34.131
I don't trust
law enforcement.

26:34.231 --> 26:36.493
Why not?

26:36.593 --> 26:40.097
You ever been homeless?

26:40.197 --> 26:42.059
No.

26:42.159 --> 26:46.483
There's a look they give you,
like you're not there.

26:48.525 --> 26:52.269
Never been homeless,
but the look --

26:52.369 --> 26:54.371
I know that look.

26:56.894 --> 26:57.835
You're a good person.

26:57.935 --> 27:00.758
I try to be.

27:00.858 --> 27:02.239
You're
a God-fearing person.

27:02.339 --> 27:03.801
Yes.

27:03.901 --> 27:06.003
And you're a person who would
leave a man bleeding out

27:06.103 --> 27:09.326
on the ground rather than risk
an encounter with the CPD.

27:09.426 --> 27:10.487
What would you had done?

27:10.587 --> 27:12.890
You don't ask the questions.

27:12.990 --> 27:15.212
It's a great question,
Your Honour.

27:15.312 --> 27:17.314
My answer?

27:20.117 --> 27:22.299
I probably would have done
the same thing.

27:22.399 --> 27:23.781
You know why?

27:23.881 --> 27:26.503
I'd be scared the cops would
accuse me of the murder.

27:26.603 --> 27:27.865
Objection.

27:27.965 --> 27:29.747
Counsel seems to be confused

27:29.847 --> 27:32.790
as to whether he's
a lawyer or a witness.

27:32.890 --> 27:35.312
What it comes down to is,

27:35.412 --> 27:37.474
who would do a thing
like that

27:37.574 --> 27:40.598
to a human face, huh?

27:40.698 --> 27:42.439
To a human head.

27:42.539 --> 27:44.541
What does it take?!

27:46.303 --> 27:49.927
There they are, all the vital
questions, all in a row,

27:50.027 --> 27:54.792
right to the very heart
of what we're doing here.

27:57.194 --> 28:00.417
Whose side are you on?

28:00.517 --> 28:09.226
♪♪

28:09.326 --> 28:14.351
♪♪

28:14.451 --> 28:16.794
Don't be scared
of me now, Jojo.

28:16.894 --> 28:24.161
♪♪

28:24.261 --> 28:29.046
♪♪

28:29.146 --> 28:30.607
We really doing this,
Ma?

28:30.707 --> 28:35.532
♪♪

28:35.632 --> 28:36.974
Scrub those potatoes.

28:37.074 --> 28:42.459
♪♪

28:42.559 --> 28:48.005
♪♪

28:51.488 --> 28:54.111
Franklin:
It's gonna be alright.

28:54.211 --> 28:57.194
Yeah, it's gonna --
it's gonna be alright.

28:57.294 --> 28:58.595
Just stay focused.

28:58.695 --> 29:01.478
Stay focused.

29:01.578 --> 29:05.042
♪♪

29:05.142 --> 29:06.924
[Footsteps approaching]

29:07.024 --> 29:08.125
There he is.

29:08.225 --> 29:09.767
Joshua: Come on, Ma.

29:09.867 --> 29:18.335
♪♪

29:18.435 --> 29:20.657
Hey, hey.

29:20.757 --> 29:22.459
For the nausea.

29:22.559 --> 29:24.301
Nausea.
Yeah.

29:24.401 --> 29:25.582
There you go.

29:25.682 --> 29:27.384
Good to see you.

29:27.484 --> 29:28.986
You good?
Yep.

29:29.086 --> 29:32.429
Good,
'cause I am starving.

29:32.529 --> 29:35.672
Hey, what's up?
[Chuckling]

29:35.772 --> 29:37.074
To the man of the hour.

29:37.174 --> 29:40.477
[Phil and Franklin laugh]

29:40.577 --> 29:44.882
♪♪

29:44.982 --> 29:46.964
Phil: Mmm-mmm!

29:47.064 --> 29:51.008
Listen, since nobody's gonna
say it,

29:51.108 --> 29:53.530
this is delicious, baby.

29:53.630 --> 29:56.053
Right?
I mean --

29:56.153 --> 29:57.414
-Good.
-Right?

29:57.514 --> 29:59.616
-I'm glad.
-Yeah.

29:59.716 --> 30:01.578
Norma:
Joshua, eat your food.

30:01.678 --> 30:02.820
Yo, you know,
one of the few memories

30:02.920 --> 30:05.542
I have of my mom
is her cooking,

30:05.642 --> 30:09.066
but she used to dance
while she cooked.

30:09.166 --> 30:13.791
An-any-anything in --
in particular?

30:13.891 --> 30:15.272
Her lamb stew.

30:15.372 --> 30:16.273
Off the chain, yeah.

30:16.373 --> 30:18.375
No.
I meant --

30:20.777 --> 30:22.800
You meant
what she was dancing to?

30:22.900 --> 30:24.161
[Laughing]

30:24.261 --> 30:26.203
The Stylistics.

30:26.303 --> 30:28.165
Mm-hmm.
And The Drifters.

30:28.265 --> 30:30.567
"Save the Last Dance For Me."
Yeah.

30:30.667 --> 30:35.873
She would play it over and over
and over and over again.

30:38.876 --> 30:40.657
I'm sorry.
Just a little nausea.

30:40.757 --> 30:43.140
Baby, baby, hey, hey, you okay?

30:43.240 --> 30:44.341
Yeah.
I'm sorry.

30:44.441 --> 30:47.905
Let me get your medicine.
No, no, no.

30:48.005 --> 30:50.027
You sure?
I'm okay.

30:50.127 --> 30:52.950
She got that morning sickness
in the evening.

30:53.050 --> 30:56.113
Hmm.

30:56.213 --> 31:00.117
Uh, did you have the same thing
with Moses and Joshua?

31:00.217 --> 31:01.558
No.

31:01.658 --> 31:02.920
First time.

31:03.020 --> 31:05.022
That probably means
it's a girl, y'all.

31:07.704 --> 31:10.127
Hey, Franklin, those meds
you were taking --

31:10.227 --> 31:11.568
is that for the cancer?

31:11.668 --> 31:13.370
Mm-hmm.

31:13.470 --> 31:16.413
What kind of meds you taking?

31:16.513 --> 31:18.775
Oh, you wouldn't -- you
wouldn't know the -- the name.

31:18.875 --> 31:21.338
No, I meant, like,
do they affect your type of --

31:21.438 --> 31:24.621
Well, do they affect your work,
side effects,

31:24.721 --> 31:27.584
something like that?

31:27.684 --> 31:30.027
I'm sorry. Was that --
That was invasive.

31:30.127 --> 31:31.588
No.
No, that was inappropriate.

31:31.688 --> 31:33.470
I-I'm sorry.

31:33.570 --> 31:35.572
I'm -- Listen.
Look.

31:40.257 --> 31:41.678
I'm sorry.
It's okay.

31:41.778 --> 31:45.242
You know, one thing I remember
about my mom --

31:45.342 --> 31:48.886
she always used to say to us,

31:48.986 --> 31:52.569
"Ask any question
you want to ask.

31:52.669 --> 31:54.211
Ain't no such thing
as too curious.

31:54.311 --> 31:55.492
Curiosity didn't kill the cat.

31:55.592 --> 31:58.455
It made the cat
everything it is."

31:58.555 --> 31:59.616
-There you go.
-Hmm?

31:59.716 --> 32:01.859
She was right.

32:01.959 --> 32:05.122
I think Phil here is a little
in awe of you, Mr. Franklin.

32:07.764 --> 32:09.066
That's why he's afraid
to ask the question

32:09.166 --> 32:11.168
he really wants to ask.

32:15.252 --> 32:17.594
How's the trial going?

32:17.694 --> 32:18.635
Yeah?

32:18.735 --> 32:20.737
Am I right?

32:23.460 --> 32:26.723
As well as a hell of a cook,
my baby's a mind reader now.

32:26.823 --> 32:29.286
[Both laughing]

32:29.386 --> 32:31.948
Just catering to my guests'
every need.

32:33.991 --> 32:36.913
Well, here's the problem.

32:38.155 --> 32:40.817
The cops took Jalil's car
to the pound.

32:40.917 --> 32:43.180
Now, why would they
do that?

32:43.280 --> 32:46.263
To clean it up, of course, down
there where no one's looking.

32:46.363 --> 32:50.867
Everybody knows impound guys
are super-cop-friendly.

32:50.967 --> 32:55.032
I just can't prove that
it was Brannigan's crew.

32:55.132 --> 32:58.395
So, you --
You know, did you, uh --

32:58.495 --> 33:00.437
So, there was
no forensics?

33:00.537 --> 33:01.878
Completely clean.

33:01.978 --> 33:03.360
No -- no fingerprints,
nothing.

33:03.460 --> 33:05.482
Uh-huh. Boy, I tell you,
them pigs --

33:05.582 --> 33:09.086
they -- they good at cleaning up
they own damn mess, now.

33:09.186 --> 33:11.248
Man. But what evidence
did you get?

33:11.348 --> 33:15.452
Between us, completely real,
not a whole lot.

33:15.552 --> 33:18.015
I-I-I got to do some --
I got to do some digging.

33:18.115 --> 33:19.176
Yeah?

33:19.276 --> 33:21.538
Digging up what?

33:21.638 --> 33:25.142
Everything turns on us
proving the cops were there --

33:25.242 --> 33:28.065
when Jalil was attacked,
straight afterwards,

33:28.165 --> 33:30.627
that they were lying
when they say they weren't.

33:30.727 --> 33:32.389
Right.

33:32.489 --> 33:35.792
I'm guessing Brannigan
spoke to all his crew

33:35.892 --> 33:38.795
on the phone sometime
after it happened,

33:38.895 --> 33:42.039
getting all of their --
their information together,

33:42.139 --> 33:45.882
marrying all their alibis,
you know.

33:45.982 --> 33:47.844
Man, I know.

33:47.944 --> 33:49.086
That damn Brannigan, man.

33:49.186 --> 33:51.808
He's a monster.

33:51.908 --> 33:53.050
Yeah.
Yeah.

33:53.150 --> 33:55.052
A monster he is.

33:55.152 --> 33:59.016
You know, I'm -- I'm going to --
I'm gonna jump him tomorrow.

33:59.116 --> 34:00.377
You say "jump him"?

34:00.477 --> 34:03.060
Uh, I'm going
to request disclosure

34:03.160 --> 34:06.183
of his phone history that night.

34:06.283 --> 34:09.066
Mm-hmm.
That's smart.

34:09.166 --> 34:11.108
Yeah, that's smart.

34:11.208 --> 34:12.589
How about you, Josh?

34:12.689 --> 34:15.672
You've been, uh,
pretty quiet tonight.

34:15.772 --> 34:18.195
[Sighs] I'm just tired.

34:18.295 --> 34:19.716
Yeah.

34:19.816 --> 34:21.818
Plumbing can be draining.

34:24.581 --> 34:26.583
Franklin: Yeah, that's him.

34:28.945 --> 34:31.328
Yeah.

34:31.428 --> 34:33.410
I'm sorry.
I'm gonna be sick.

34:33.510 --> 34:36.573
♪♪

34:36.673 --> 34:38.775
I got it, I got it.

34:38.875 --> 34:40.617
Ma.

34:40.717 --> 34:41.978
I'll -- I'll check it out.

34:42.078 --> 34:44.621
Yeah.
It's okay.

34:44.721 --> 34:46.423
Ma, Ma, you okay?

34:46.523 --> 34:51.188
[Coughing, retching]

34:51.288 --> 34:52.829
Norma, you okay?

34:52.929 --> 34:58.675
♪♪

34:58.775 --> 35:04.441
♪♪

35:04.541 --> 35:10.387
♪♪

35:15.392 --> 35:17.294
I don't want
to be doing this.

35:17.394 --> 35:19.616
It's not what we do.

35:19.716 --> 35:22.699
I'm afraid you're going
to have to.

35:22.799 --> 35:24.941
Okay.

35:25.041 --> 35:26.943
He was real messy.

35:27.043 --> 35:32.709
I mean, complicated,
dirty, ugly, messy.

35:32.809 --> 35:34.511
Drunk?

35:34.611 --> 35:36.193
Us cops can drink.

35:36.293 --> 35:39.076
You know, we can drink with
the best of them and then some.

35:39.176 --> 35:41.758
But Logan was more drunk
than I've ever seen him.

35:41.858 --> 35:44.761
Was there a reason
for that?

35:44.861 --> 35:46.963
The Moses Johnson verdict.

35:47.063 --> 35:48.605
And what did he say
about that?

35:48.705 --> 35:50.807
He was saying
what the verdict means.

35:50.907 --> 35:53.850
He said it means people
are entitled to run

35:53.950 --> 35:55.492
from a police officer

35:55.592 --> 35:57.454
and that people are entitled
to fight us

35:57.554 --> 35:59.896
when we're doing our duty.

35:59.996 --> 36:02.219
He said, "The only thing
you need

36:02.319 --> 36:04.501
to have all that
going for you --

36:04.601 --> 36:07.824
your skin has to be
the right colour."

36:07.924 --> 36:09.666
He said that?

36:09.766 --> 36:11.508
Then he went crazy.

36:11.608 --> 36:12.669
How do you mean?

36:12.769 --> 36:17.314
Incoherent, angry, wild.

36:17.414 --> 36:19.996
Have you seen him
that way before?

36:20.096 --> 36:21.518
Yes.

36:21.618 --> 36:23.360
When his partner died.

36:23.460 --> 36:25.462
He lost control then,
too.

36:27.103 --> 36:29.126
That's the thing
about being a cop.

36:29.226 --> 36:32.249
You have to have
emotional discipline.

36:32.349 --> 36:34.971
Hysteria doesn't help you
do your job.

36:35.071 --> 36:36.693
A good cop has to have it
in him

36:36.793 --> 36:40.177
to think clearly
and rationally under pressure.

36:40.277 --> 36:44.100
I thought Johnny Logan
had that. I was wrong.

36:44.200 --> 36:48.084
And in the days
after Michael Rossi's death?

36:52.609 --> 36:55.872
Lieutenant?

36:55.972 --> 36:58.875
His loss of control
turned into something else.

36:58.975 --> 37:01.198
How would you
characterise that?

37:01.298 --> 37:06.243
With an old Irish word --
bogán.

37:06.343 --> 37:09.005
It means "an egg
without a shell."

37:09.105 --> 37:13.650
It used to describe mushy food
or soft ground.

37:13.750 --> 37:17.414
But sometimes, my grandfather
used it about his brother.

37:17.514 --> 37:21.938
He meant spineless,
without backbone.

37:22.038 --> 37:24.040
And that was Logan then?

37:26.843 --> 37:29.105
Can you be specific?

37:29.205 --> 37:36.953
♪♪

37:37.053 --> 37:38.315
No.

37:38.415 --> 37:41.037
"No" you can't
or "no" you won't?

37:41.137 --> 37:42.239
I don't want to go there.

37:42.339 --> 37:44.201
Yes, you can
and, yes, you will.

37:44.301 --> 37:47.284
What was Officer Logan saying
that made him

37:47.384 --> 37:50.487
lead you to the conclusion
he was spineless?

37:50.587 --> 37:53.490
It's what he was doing,
not saying.

37:53.590 --> 37:55.772
What was he doing,
Lieutenant?

37:55.872 --> 37:58.855
♪♪

37:58.955 --> 38:01.618
Lieutenant?

38:01.718 --> 38:04.581
Having an affair
with Jessica Rossi.

38:04.681 --> 38:06.863
What?

38:06.963 --> 38:08.825
His dead partner's wife?

38:08.925 --> 38:11.668
♪♪

38:11.768 --> 38:12.789
Yes.

38:12.889 --> 38:14.911
I'm sorry.

38:15.011 --> 38:16.953
Yes.

38:17.053 --> 38:19.476
♪♪

38:19.576 --> 38:22.679
Franklin: What the hell?!
Really?

38:22.779 --> 38:25.041
I mean,
what were you thinking?

38:25.141 --> 38:32.168
♪♪

38:32.268 --> 38:39.336
♪♪

38:39.436 --> 38:46.603
♪♪

38:52.609 --> 38:56.673
Lieutenant Brannigan says
you have an explanation.

38:56.773 --> 38:58.395
I can't imagine
what that would be,

38:58.495 --> 39:00.036
and he wouldn't tell me,

39:00.136 --> 39:03.520
because he said it should
come from you and not him.

39:03.620 --> 39:06.162
But if you have a reason
why you gave Roberts

39:06.262 --> 39:08.865
that tape, it would help
everyone to hear it.

39:13.149 --> 39:15.592
We don't want to stop
supporting your family.

39:17.914 --> 39:19.936
We really don't.

39:20.036 --> 39:23.019
We're trying to be
good people here,

39:23.119 --> 39:25.101
but it's hard.

39:25.201 --> 39:27.384
So think about it,
Mrs. Rossi.

39:27.484 --> 39:30.387
But not for too long.

39:30.487 --> 39:32.148
We need to be made whole.

39:32.248 --> 39:39.716
♪♪

39:39.816 --> 39:41.818
[Can falls]

39:42.779 --> 39:45.802
So, the night of...

39:45.902 --> 39:49.606
I had a couple of drinks
and left the bar early.

39:49.706 --> 39:52.529
Why?
I don't understand.

39:52.629 --> 39:54.170
Well, on a night
like that,

39:54.270 --> 39:57.374
with all the stress and trauma
of the Moses verdict.

39:57.474 --> 39:59.295
That's exactly why.

39:59.395 --> 40:01.257
How do you mean?
I wanted to be at home,

40:01.357 --> 40:04.501
'cause I knew
I'd be getting lots of calls.

40:04.601 --> 40:06.262
I'm a kind of
father figure

40:06.362 --> 40:08.304
to a lot of cops
in my district.

40:08.404 --> 40:09.906
They come to me
when they're in trouble.

40:10.006 --> 40:12.829
But why would that mean
you had to be at home?

40:12.929 --> 40:15.031
Away from Logan's
craziness.

40:15.131 --> 40:16.633
I wanted to hear myself think

40:16.733 --> 40:18.194
so I could be there
for my guys.

40:18.294 --> 40:20.757
Mm-hmm. Did you
take calls that night?

40:20.857 --> 40:23.760
Lots.
From?

40:23.860 --> 40:27.924
Frater, Young,
Gallagher, all my guys.

40:28.024 --> 40:31.007
Do you have your phone history
from that night?

40:31.107 --> 40:32.929
Yes, I do.

40:33.029 --> 40:36.493
Do you recall where
Officer Frater called you from?

40:36.593 --> 40:37.534
His home.

40:37.634 --> 40:39.295
At what time?

40:39.395 --> 40:41.257
Around 7:00.

40:41.357 --> 40:45.382
That's an hour before the 911
call for Jalil came in.

40:45.482 --> 40:47.384
Is that right?
Sounds right.

40:47.484 --> 40:48.945
Gallagher?
Young?

40:49.045 --> 40:51.588
I think Frater was
the first to call.

40:51.688 --> 40:54.270
So all the other guys
would have been after 8:00.

40:54.370 --> 40:55.872
Thank you so much.

40:55.972 --> 41:05.141
♪♪

41:09.025 --> 41:11.207
Dr. Algren: Yeah, give me that
scan and the other one

41:11.307 --> 41:13.009
and put it on my desk.

41:13.109 --> 41:15.632
Okay. Alright.

41:18.314 --> 41:21.257
[Tires screech]

41:21.357 --> 41:23.339
Dr. Algren?
Come with us, please.

41:23.439 --> 41:24.621
-Wh-- wh--
-Now.

41:24.721 --> 41:27.383
Hey, hey, hey!
Where are you taking me?

41:27.483 --> 41:28.945
-Let's go.
-Hey!

41:29.045 --> 41:36.192
♪♪

41:36.292 --> 41:43.720
♪♪

41:43.820 --> 41:51.247
♪♪

41:51.347 --> 41:59.936
♪♪

42:00.036 --> 42:06.302
♪♪

42:06.402 --> 42:12.669
♪♪

42:12.769 --> 42:16.953
Prescribed
and proscribed.

42:17.053 --> 42:20.276
I always struggled
with the difference.

42:20.376 --> 42:24.240
But I got it now.
At least I think I do.

42:24.340 --> 42:28.525
Prescribe means
issuing meds to people.

42:28.625 --> 42:30.887
Proscribed means meds

42:30.987 --> 42:33.730
you're not allowed
to prescribe.

42:33.830 --> 42:36.653
Have I got that right?

42:36.753 --> 42:40.937
And a doctor who's confused
about the difference --

42:41.037 --> 42:43.940
what would happen to him?

42:44.040 --> 42:47.063
What do you want?

42:47.163 --> 42:49.906
I've always liked a doctor
who gets right down to it.

42:50.006 --> 42:55.071
♪♪

42:55.171 --> 42:57.714
How long has he got?

42:57.814 --> 43:02.999
♪♪

43:03.099 --> 43:06.763
Weeks, not months.

43:06.863 --> 43:10.126
He don't look
as bad as that.

43:10.226 --> 43:12.448
That's why he wanted
the medication.

43:12.548 --> 43:19.255
♪♪

43:19.355 --> 43:20.577
You can go now.

43:20.677 --> 43:25.542
♪♪

43:25.642 --> 43:30.506
♪♪

43:30.606 --> 43:32.308
[Engine starts]

43:32.408 --> 43:35.391
♪♪

43:35.491 --> 43:37.914
The doctor says he's on his way
out and quickly.

43:38.014 --> 43:41.157
But I'd rest a lot easier
with our thumb on the scale.

43:41.257 --> 43:43.279
I got an idea.

43:43.379 --> 43:45.201
Leonard:
So, what is it?

43:45.301 --> 43:46.803
I'm gonna go see
an old friend.

43:46.903 --> 43:54.891
♪♪

43:54.991 --> 43:58.494
[Indistinct conversations]

43:58.594 --> 44:00.016
He's back.

44:00.116 --> 44:03.179
Did you miss me?

44:03.279 --> 44:04.941
Squeeze.

44:05.041 --> 44:06.823
My man.

44:06.923 --> 44:08.184
Man: 118 up.

44:08.284 --> 44:09.826
How you been, bro?

44:09.926 --> 44:12.949
I'm good.

44:13.049 --> 44:14.671
Where's your boy?

44:14.771 --> 44:16.633
Where's my boy?

44:16.733 --> 44:19.475
You hit the nail
right on the head.

44:19.575 --> 44:22.478
On his way to hell,
where he belongs.

44:22.578 --> 44:25.081
I need you to help me
send him there.

44:25.181 --> 44:28.304
You know how much I enjoy
playing with cops.

44:30.907 --> 44:33.249
Johnny: Say it again.
Say that again!

44:33.349 --> 44:35.171
Brannigan: Get in the car.
Logan --

44:35.271 --> 44:37.333
Judge Evans:
Six months ago,

44:37.433 --> 44:41.257
outside a fried-chicken joint
on 55th Street.

44:41.357 --> 44:43.339
Say it again!
That's enough!

44:43.439 --> 44:44.380
Say that again!

44:44.480 --> 44:47.904
Get off of him!

44:48.004 --> 44:50.226
Someone posted this online.

44:50.326 --> 44:52.148
The link was sent to three
members of the jury,

44:52.248 --> 44:54.470
who all watched it
in its entirety.

44:54.570 --> 44:55.992
Sent by whom?

44:56.092 --> 44:58.835
We suspect the e-mail was sent
by juror number 9.

44:58.935 --> 45:01.998
He claims his computer was
hacked, denies any involvement.

45:02.098 --> 45:03.439
I've ordered an investigation.

45:03.539 --> 45:05.682
Just a blatant attempt
to delay the trial,

45:05.782 --> 45:08.404
Your Honour.
Delay?

45:08.504 --> 45:10.506
Why would anyone do that?

45:12.468 --> 45:16.092
Look, regardless of the motive,
the jury has been compromised.

45:16.192 --> 45:17.854
Even if I were to seat
the three alternates,

45:17.954 --> 45:19.295
we'd still be short one juror,

45:19.395 --> 45:21.898
because I'm now forced
to remove number 9.

45:21.998 --> 45:24.220
I want this
to be a fair trial.

45:24.320 --> 45:26.622
It's way too important
for it not to be.

45:26.722 --> 45:27.984
There's no way you
could watch that video

45:28.084 --> 45:29.345
and not be biased.

45:29.445 --> 45:30.586
So we're looking
at a mistrial.

45:30.686 --> 45:31.908
Mm-hmm.

45:32.008 --> 45:33.269
When would the new trial be?

45:33.369 --> 45:36.632
At least four months,
probably six.

45:36.732 --> 45:45.962
♪♪

45:46.062 --> 45:47.844
Only one thing
matters here.

45:47.944 --> 45:51.087
My client stands to lose
from the members of the jury

45:51.187 --> 45:52.729
watching this video.

45:52.829 --> 45:56.092
♪♪

45:56.192 --> 45:59.135
So the choice is his.

45:59.235 --> 46:04.060
Does he want to continue
or ask for a mistrial?

46:04.160 --> 46:06.943
♪♪

46:07.043 --> 46:08.584
Officer?

46:08.684 --> 46:11.948
♪♪

46:12.048 --> 46:15.531
I, uh --
I need some time.

46:16.572 --> 46:19.796
Okay.
Back here tomorrow morning.

46:19.896 --> 46:22.038
I want your decision then.

46:22.138 --> 46:25.281
Thank you, Your Honour.
Thank you, Your Honour.

46:25.381 --> 46:26.402
♪ And we buckin' back ♪

46:26.502 --> 46:28.885
♪ 16 shots ♪

46:28.985 --> 46:30.046
♪ 16 shots ♪

46:30.146 --> 46:31.768
What do you think
he'll do?

46:31.868 --> 46:33.289
I don't know.

46:33.389 --> 46:36.652
I'm -- I'm not allowing myself
to think the worst.

46:36.752 --> 46:37.974
♪ 16 shots ♪

46:38.074 --> 46:39.375
Okay, okay.

46:39.475 --> 46:41.738
You can watch something else,
you know?

46:41.838 --> 46:42.979
Like what?

46:43.079 --> 46:44.580
Something lighthearted.

46:44.680 --> 46:46.062
"Breaking Bad," maybe?

46:46.162 --> 46:49.425
I don't know.
Here.

46:49.525 --> 46:51.948
I think you just put
your foot in this,

46:52.048 --> 46:53.589
and then you pull.

46:53.689 --> 46:54.991
Try it.

46:55.091 --> 46:57.113
There. There.

46:57.213 --> 47:03.119
♪♪

47:03.219 --> 47:05.221
There it is.

47:08.064 --> 47:09.325
There.

47:09.425 --> 47:18.534
♪♪

47:18.634 --> 47:21.097
Franklin: Doc Martens,
early 2000s.

47:21.197 --> 47:23.019
Look familiar?

47:23.119 --> 47:25.061
Yes!

47:25.161 --> 47:26.702
Bingo.

47:26.802 --> 47:32.748
♪♪

47:32.848 --> 47:35.591
Brannigan w-was there.

47:35.691 --> 47:37.874
We got him.

47:37.974 --> 47:43.719
♪♪

47:43.819 --> 47:49.485
♪♪

47:49.585 --> 47:52.688
Um, Peter Sessions
at the news desk. Is he in?

47:52.788 --> 47:56.332
Um...yep.

47:56.432 --> 47:58.895
Could you make sure
he gets this?

47:58.995 --> 48:00.536
Fine.

48:00.636 --> 48:06.022
♪♪

48:06.122 --> 48:11.547
♪♪

48:11.647 --> 48:12.668
Franklin?

48:12.768 --> 48:14.150
It's done.

48:14.250 --> 48:18.754
♪♪

